## **************************************
## Newton's laws, Ch5, problem 46, D'Agostino, 12 May 2017
## 
## **************************************
$g=9.8;
$m=5;
$A=32;
$a=$g*(sin(pi*$A/180));
$t=0.8;
$d=0.5*$a*($t)**2;

#$string = image('k_q1.png',width => 200, height => '', extra_html_tags =>
#'align="middle"', tex_size => 400);
#TEXT($string.$PAR);

BEGIN_TEXT 
A block of mass \(5\) kg is placed on a frictionless ramp that is inclined at an angle of \(32^{\circ}\) with respect to the horizontal, and then released and slides down the ramp.   $BR

$PAR
(a) Determine the magnitude of the acceleration of the block. $BR

\{ ans_rule(20) \} m/s<sup>2</sup>
$PAR
END_TEXT 

ANS( num_cmp($a)); 

BEGIN_TEXT
$PAR
(b) Determine how far the block slides down the ramp in \(0.8\) s. $BR

\{ ans_rule(20) \} m
$PAR
END_TEXT

ANS( num_cmp($d));


